# Frontend — TypeScript (`.ts`)

Same principles as `.tsx` in this repo: Next.js 14 App Router, `camelCase` / `PascalCase` for types and components, API calls consistent with neighboring files.

- Handlers in `app/**/route.ts` — export `GET` / `POST` / …; request/response types aligned with the backend API.
- Avoid extra dependencies; Tailwind belongs in components — `.ts` files are usually logic and fetch calls.
